text.__SUMMARY__: Grevillea costata is a shrub of the genus Grevillea native to an area along the west coast of the Mid West region of Western Australia.The shrub is spreading with many branches and typically grows to a height of 0.8 to 1.5 metres (3 to 5 ft) in height and has non-glaucous branchlets that are angular and ridged and sericeous between ridges.
